Form1-PanelLeftTree-TreeView1-Hint.ENG: Tree view of parameters of current device. Click any group of parameters or index to view.

Form1-Panel2-TabControl1-ButtonConnect-H.ENG: Press this button to connect to selected device. If you connected to this device earlier then dictionary will be loaded from file on disk. Otherwise dictionary will be loaded from device.

Form1-Panel2-TabControl1-ButtonReconnect.ENG:
If button is blinking you should update dictionary because dictionary saved in file on disk doesn't match dictionary in device.
Even if device ID (parameter 1018h) matches, dictionaries sometimes can be different and dictionary loaded from file doesn't match current device. This button forcibly loads dictionary directly from device. Besides, it is necessary to update dictionary if nominal (rated) values changed (for example nominal speed, current etc).

At the moment, the test mode is turned off.

FormTestMode-PageControlTests-TabSheet2-.ENG: Attention! Don't use this mode, if you don't know what you are doing. If you select nonzero test number then inverter power switches will be open. It can lead to device failure if load is connected.

FormParamLoad-PanelBottom-ButtonCompare-.ENG: Compare two dictionaries - loaded from file on disk and loaded from current device to analize which parameters can be loaded from file to device. If some parameters missed or have different format - they won't be selected and corresponding message will be printed in diagnostic window.

FormParamLoad-PanelBottom-CheckBoxReload.ENG: Update dictionary of device before comparison

To ensure correct structure of CANopen dictionary it is recommended to update the dictionary via loading it from device. However it can take a lot of time. If you are sure that dictionary of current device is correct (firmware wasn't changed or dictionary was updated recently), this option may be cleared.

FormConnectParametrs-GroupBox1-GroupBox4.ENG: Enables querying for UINT32 parameter 2600h.01 (Vendor Token). It is recommended to enable this option only if network has device(s) which have this object in its CANopen dictionary. Vendor Token is used to identify the file with CANopen texts in network where there are devices from different manufacturers. If the device has this parameter in its dictionary, and it is not zero, then the texts for this device will be loaded from file 'coTextBase_XXXXXXXX.xml' where XXXXXXXX is the Vendor Token (as hexadecimal number). If this parameter is missing or it has a zero value, the texts will be loaded from a file 'coTextBase.xml'.

_3317522370.ENG:
How properly load firmware to device and save/restore it's current parameters? To do this: 1. Update dictionary. 2. Save parameters to file on disk: Service->Parameters transfer->Save to file. 3. Load new firmware to device: Service->Programming. 4. Update dictionary. 5. Load saved parameters from file: Service->Parameters transfer->Load from file. 6. Save parameters to device EEPROM: button "Save parameters" in upper right part of main window. 7. Reboot device. 8. Update dictionary. Done!
Why is it so complicated? All parameters are stored in device EEPROM. When firmware is updatated the number of parameters may changed (if programmer added or removed some parameters). As a result, device can't use parameters from EEPROM saved here before firmware update because it's number changed. So device reset all parameters to it's default values. UniCON application when loading parameters from file acts more elegantly: application searches parameters which were added/removed and loads only unchanged parameters to device. Why update dictionary several times? First dictionary update is needed if you started work with unknown device, to load parameters list from device. Second dictionary update is needed after firmware update, to load parameters list of new firmware. Third dictionary update is needed after device reset all parameters to default values, because some parameters are so called 'base' or 'nominal' (rated voltage, rated current, rated speed and so on). Such base parameters are used by application to properly scale and display PU-parameters (rated to nominal/base parameters). After third dictionary update application gets actual values of such base parameters. In some cases you can skip some steps. But you should understand what you do! For example, if you are sure that parameters list didn't changed in new firmware, or if you don't need to restore previous values of parameters.

BootloaderActivatorForm-HelpLabel1-Capti.ENG: This function is intended for devices with embedded CAN-bootloader. The main function of such a bootloader is to restore the operability of the device via the CAN network (without direct access to device) after unsuccessful firmware, for example, due to a power failure. When the device is turned on, the bootloader listens to the CAN network for 100 ms at a speed of 125 kbps waiting for a special message. If such a message appears, the bootloader delegates control to the programmer module, which becomes visible in the CAN network as a node with name "CAN_prog". You can connect to this node in a standard way and flash the software. Since the bootloader only listens to the CAN line and can't set confirmation (acknowledge), then for successful message delivery you need to have two CAN-devices. As a second device, you can use, for example, the second channel of CAN-bus-USB adapter (Marathon) with the "canwise" utility running on PC.

BootloaderActivatorForm-HelpLabel2-Capti.ENG: So, follow the next steps to activate the CAN bootloader: 1. Check that the data transfer rate is set to 125 kbps in the communication module settings. 2. Make sure that there is at least one more device in the CAN network besides the target device. 3. Press the "Start" button below - a special message will be broadcast into the CAN network (with period of 50 ms). 4. Reboot the target device (via reset button or power off/on). 5. In case of successful activation of the bootloader, the device named "CAN_prog" should appear in the list of available nodes. 6. Close the activation window. 7. Connect to the "CAN_prog" node and flash it as usual.
